<p><strong><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/San+Blas+Islands/@9.5785156,-78.808389,12.54z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x8e54faf5fbdb641d:0x63414c65f5844d1c!8m2!3d9.5703192!4d-78.7872015" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">The San Blas Islands are located</a></strong> off the Caribbean coast of Eastern Panama, which means clear, warm seas!&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>The archipelago is roughly 145 kilometers (90 miles) away from <strong><a href="https://destinationlesstravel.com/things-to-do-in-panama-city-panama/">Panama City</a></strong>, which is where most people travel from.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>Getting to the San Blas Islands from Panama City is surprisingly easy &ndash; you&rsquo;ll be picked up early in a 4&times;4 and head to Puerto de Carti. There, you board a boat that takes you straight to the islands. Easy peasy!&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>The San Blas Islands are also relatively close to <strong><a href="https://destinationlesstravel.com/things-to-do-in-cartagena-colombia/">Cartagena, Colombia</a></strong>. There&rsquo;s a 373-kilometer (231-mile) distance between the two, so it&rsquo;s possible to visit from here.&nbsp;</p>



