<p>The San Blas Islands have a pretty long rainy season, which runs from May to December. The dry season, from January to April, is the ideal time to go, but this does give you a pretty narrow window.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The good news is that the wet season doesn&rsquo;t mean it&rsquo;s going to rain all day every day &ndash; but it does mean you will probably experience at least a few pretty heavy downpours while you&rsquo;re there. However, they don&rsquo;t usually last more than an hour or two. </p>



<p>The islands are also quieter during the wet season, which some people find makes up for the rain.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>October and November are the wettest months, so maybe try to avoid these if you can. Obviously, the dry season is ideal, but if you&rsquo;re visiting from May to September, your trip is unlikely to be spoiled by bad weather.&nbsp;</p>



