<p>It&rsquo;s a pretty easy journey from both cities and there are plenty of <strong><a href="https://destinationlesstravel.com/tours-in-panama-city/">tours from Panama City</a></strong> and Cartagena that will handle everything for you.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>With that being said, most tour companies don&rsquo;t offer a return trip from Cartagena, so you&rsquo;ll want to make sure you&rsquo;ve had your fill of that city and all the <strong><a href="https://destinationlesstravel.com/tours-in-cartagena-colombia/">amazing tours in Cartagena</a></strong> before leaving. Typically tours to the San Blas Islands take you from Cartagena to the San Blas Islands and then continue on to Panama City, or vice versa.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>However, if Cartagena is not on your travel itinerary, then there are plenty of tours that offer a return trip from Panama City.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



