<p>If you&rsquo;re a bit pressed for time, Tao Travel 365 also offers&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://www.viator.com/tours/San-Blas-Islands/NEWLY-OPENED-San-Blas-Islands-PRIV-Cabin-Over-the-Water-2-days-1-night-Tour/d4516-127626P40?pid=P00050132&amp;mcid=42383&amp;medium=link&amp;campaign=ttk-san-blas-islands" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">this shorter San Blas Island tour</a></strong>. </p>



<p>You&rsquo;ll get to stay in an overwater cabin, which is an incredibly cool experience. Plus, you&rsquo;ll take a boat tour around the islands. </p>



<p>Snorkel gear is included and you&rsquo;ll get to snorkel at amazing places like Isla Perro with its sunken shipwreck and look for sea stars on the ocean floor. </p>



<p>All your transportation, meals, accommodation, and activities are included for the incredible $165 USD cost. You&rsquo;ll still need to pay the entrance fee to the region and any drinks you buy, but this tour is a steal!</p>



<p>This 2-day San Blas Island is very popular, so you should <strong><a href="https://www.viator.com/tours/San-Blas-Islands/NEWLY-OPENED-San-Blas-Islands-PRIV-Cabin-Over-the-Water-2-days-1-night-Tour/d4516-127626P40?pid=P00050132&amp;mcid=42383&amp;medium=link&amp;campaign=ttk-san-blas-islands" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">book it online well in advance</a></strong>. </p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">San Blas Island Day Tour&nbsp;&nbsp;</h4>



<p>If you&rsquo;re REALLY pressed for time, then you can even take&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://www.viator.com/en-CA/tours/Panama-City/Day-Tour-in-San-Blas-Islands-All-Included-Visit-3-Islands-in-1-Day/d950-75405P1?pid=P00050132&amp;mcid=42383&amp;medium=link&amp;campaign=ttk-san-blas-islands" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">this day tour&nbsp;of the San Blas Islands</a></strong> from Panama City. </p>



<p>You&rsquo;ll get to snorkel, visit 3-4 of the prettiest islands, kayak or paddle board, and enjoy a traditional lunch. One of the islands you&rsquo;ll visit is Isla Perro, where you&rsquo;ll get to participate in a game of volleyball with the locals.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Everything is taken care of for you, so this is a super convenient way to visit the San Blas Islands if you don&rsquo;t have a lot of time to spare.&nbsp;At $160 USD, it&rsquo;s a similar price as the overnight tour, but this tour lasts 14 hours (with a 5 am pick up!) and returns you back to Panama City in the evening. </p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Colombia to Panama/Vice Versa&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Blue Sailing&nbsp;&nbsp;</h4>



<p><strong><a href="https://www.bluesailing.net/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Blue Sailing</a></strong>&nbsp;is a tour company that specializes in the San Blas Islands, so you better believe they know what they&rsquo;re doing!&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>The trip is about 5 nights long with 3 days spent island-hopping around the San Blas Islands and then one travel day on either side of your trip for the open sea crossing. </p>



<p>You&rsquo;ll stay on a sailboat the whole time and enjoy fresh, local food as you cruise around the archipelago. You&rsquo;ll sleep in bunk accommodation and shower time is limited &ndash; this is a pretty rustic experience, but it&rsquo;s also a lot of fun.&nbsp;</p>



<p>You can take a <strong><a href="https://www.bluesailing.net/panama-to-cartagena/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">tour&nbsp;from Panama City</a></strong> to the San Blas Islands&nbsp;and then on to Cartagena, or&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://www.bluesailing.net/cartagena-to-panama/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">vice versa starting in Columbia</a></strong>. No matter where your trip starts from, you&rsquo;ll sail around, glimpsing some of the archipelago&rsquo;s most remote, uninhabited islands and there&rsquo;s plenty of snorkeling, fishing, and beach time to enjoy.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Expect to pay around $600-700 USD per person &ndash; it varies depending on the season you book and the boat you&rsquo;re on.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Island tour&nbsp;&nbsp;</h4>



<p>San Blas Adventures also offers a <strong><a href="https://sanblasadventures.com/boat-colombia-to-panama/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">boat&nbsp;tour from Colombia to Panama</a></strong>. You&rsquo;ll travel on a fast boat rather than a sailboat, so there&rsquo;s no 2-day ocean crossing.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>You&rsquo;ll spend more time on the islands than you will on the boat, so you really get to experience the best of San Blas. In fact, you only spend a total of 8 hours on the boat over the course of 4 days!&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>There&rsquo;ll be lots of time to interact with the locals and learn more about the island communities that make the San Blas Islands so fascinating.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>This tour is $465 USD during the non-busy months, $495 USD during high season (Dec-March) and there&rsquo;s a special Christmas/New Year&rsquo;s trip for $595 USD. </p>



